Hmm. That error suggests you tried to convert a string slice (`&str`) into some sort of `Result`, but that isn't valid. If you want to return an error or success with strings, make sure your function signature matches. Try something like:

```rust
fn from_str(s: &str) -> Result<String, &'static str> {
    Ok(s.to_string())
}
```
or if you want an actual error variant:

```rust
fn from_str(s: &str) -> Result<String, String> {
    Err("Invalid input".to_string())
}
```
Choose one based on what you want to represent.
